    "created_at": "2016-03-01T12:11:53Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-01T12:18:29Z",
    "body": "well, after switching, electron will depend on the maintained library called GTK3 and and no longer on the legacy library called GTK2.\n\na system without $library installed will require you to install $library to use a software depending on $library. ATM electron needs you to have GTK2 (and many other things) installed, after this GTK3 (and many other things). it’s the packagers’ job to get the dependencies right.\n\ni don’t think there is such a thing as a “GTK2 system”. all GTK-based desktop environments on linux (including the GNOME2 fork MATE) are GTK3 based. only some projects with big inertia which are hard to port still use GTK2.\n"
  },
