    "created_at": "2016-03-01T12:37:36Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-01T12:39:40Z",
    "body": "well, you’re simply following what chromium does. if chromium changes one of its dependencies, will you freeze the chromium version you use because of that?\n\nbtw., what do you mean, “degrade gracefully”? link to GTK2 if GTK3 can’t be found? that’ll be a load of headaches once we (inevitably) start relying on GTK3 features.\n\nfwiw, @zcbenz said in #2927:\n\n> Sounds good to me after we upgraded to Chrome 47.\n\nas for other advantages: it will look better and integrate into the system look, have a better file picker and so on. it’s a big usability win, having support for new UI features like hi-res displays, scrolling behavior, …\n"
  },
