    "created_at": "2016-03-01T13:23:07Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-01T13:24:44Z",
    "body": "good points, except that i’m extremely sure that people who don’t use _any_ GTK3 thing also won’t use electron, and both MATE and Xfce use GTK3. (while LXDE is switching to Qt)\n\ni just can’t see a single person who’d use exclusively LXDE-apps, chromium, and electron apps (everything else already switched to GTK3). LXDE stuff is for extremely memory-limited systems, exactly where chromium and electron _don’t_ fit.\n\neveryone using libreoffice, firefox, or any GTK-based DE except for LXDE is using GTK3 already.\n"
